		<div class="post" id="post-1855638">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1855638)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1855638">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1552358&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227291" alt="HammerMaiden" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1552358)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;" >HammerMaiden</a></span> <span class="odate time_1379692503 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Sep 2013 15:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1855638">
									

<p>Okay. If you'd rather have a public discussion about this, that's perfectly acceptable.</p>
<p>I think in this particular case, the definitions used are applied too rigidly. Dr. Thaddeus Xyank is a character whose story I have already begun to establish elsewhere on the site (See <a href="/iteration-0">Iteration 0</a> and <a href="/the-deep-end">The Deep End</a>). This document can be read as another meaningful chapter in his understanding of temporal anomalies and his work with them. It also is written, quite clearly, in the style of a Welcome Letter, meant for general distribution among newly recruited members of RCTF-Δt. It is definitely an orientation by its very nature.</p>
<p>It is, however, <em>also</em> a supplemental document recovered by an alternate version of the Foundation. SCP-1780 showed up in the dirt somewhere on Foundation property decades ago. This Foundation has no temporal anomalies department, and so instead of accepting it as a legitimate part of the Foundation's operation and mission, they have done the prudent thing and contained it. Document 1780-WL is a transcript of documentation recovered from within that anomaly, which needs to be kept and studied and contained in its own right. As such, it is classified as a supplement to the SCP-1780 document.</p>
<p>In the greater SCPniverse, <em>both</em> of these versions of the Foundation exist, simultaneously. It is up to the reader to decide, then, which is more interesting and which is more valid. The wiki itself cannot make that judgement for them by relegating this document to one domain or another.</p>
<p>SCP-1780 and this document represent an attempt to bring the idea that &quot;nothing is canon, so everything is canon&quot; into the reader's mind and give it a bigger sandbox to play in. Given the function of RCTF-Δt and what they do to fracture/repair causality, the idea that several contradictory realities and story-lines can exist simultaneously is given legitimacy.</p>
<p><em>That's</em> why it should be tagged as both.</p>

							</div>

								
					
